cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR. 

This paper is about semantic parsing, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. Within cs.CL, the paper could also fit into cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper proposes a neural architecture, which suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on four datasets, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as a possible category as well.
